    <p>Across all five, the pattern is the same shape at different volumes: the cockatoo trades the Grey's talking and independence for contact and showmanship. The Galah asks the least of you, the Moluccan the most, and the Grey sits apart from all of them as the one you can hold a conversation with.</p>
